# Cost, usage, and unit-economics telemetry

## Rule

Any feature that consumes paid APIs, compute, storage, bandwidth, background jobs,
or user quota must emit usage in one canonical, auditable path.

## Telemetry contract

1. Emit from one authoritative site per billable action.
2. Use a run/job/request/user/org scope ID that survives retries.
3. Make emission idempotent with a stable key.
4. Record provider, model/service, unit type, quantity, price basis, currency,
   timestamp, and source subsystem when known.
5. Never trust client-reported cost or quota consumption without server-side
   verification.
6. Degrade safely when telemetry tables/columns are missing during deploy skew.
7. Make retries distinguish original attempt, retry attempt, and final charged
   usage.
8. Keep audit records separate from display summaries.

## Unit economics

If public pricing, plan limits, credits, free quotas, or margins are changed,
update:

- Billing config.
- Entitlement gates.
- Metering logic.
- Public copy.
- Tests.
- Seed/bootstrap scripts.
- Any reconciliation job.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] One authoritative emit site.
- [ ] Stable idempotency key.
- [ ] Server-side quantity/cost basis.
- [ ] Plan limits and public copy match runtime behavior.
